life as a bachelor life as a married person which is most enjoyable why do you think so they each have their ups and downs singleness is great because you are completely independent and you have the freedom to be a little selfish sometimes if you want to stay up until am watching oprah reruns no one will care that you're not in bed if you want to stay out late with your friends or take a weekend getaway on a whim no one will be bothered if you don't come home that night you get to date around if you're into that sort of thing and experience the variety of meeting different types of people in that way you can decorate your apartment however you want without worrying that someone won't like your choice of sofa the world is yours and you don't have anyone's feelings to consider but your own then again married life has tons of positives too assuming that you made a good choice in your life partner you have a best friend someone who loves you unconditionally and loved you enough to commit to you for a lifetime you have someone to share your joys help shoulder your sorrows and lighten the load of life you have someone to make love to and someone to hold at night someone who knows you better than anyone else and loves your flaws as much as your strengths basically you have a soulmate and you get to experience a depth of intimacy that can't be experienced any other way you may even be granted the joy of having children with that person and seeing a little of them each time you look into the face of your child you have a partner and possibly a family who completes you i've known single people who complain about their lonliness and married people who complain about their lack of freedom my opinion embrace the period of life you're in right now singleness is a blessing and so is married life wherever you are on your own journey just enjoy the ride it's a philosophy that's worked pretty well for me so far anyway hope that helps Polyamory Current teachings of Prem Rawat The Eman